
Software needed:

- Android SDK ( http://developer.android.com/sdk/ )
- scala 2.11 ( http://www.scala-lang.org/ )
- scas 2.1 ( http://github.com/rjolly/scas/ )

For the conduit:

- Sqlite JDBC Driver ( http://www.xerial.org/maven/repository/artifact/org/xerial/sqlite-jdbc/3.7.2/sqlite-jdbc-3.7.2.jar )


To build scas-android on android sdk:

  java -Dscas.home=$SCAS_HOME -Dscala.home=$SCALA_HOME -jar $ANDROID_HOME/tools/proguard/lib/proguard.jar @proguard.cfg
  ant release


To run the conduit, add the conduit directory to your path, give conduit/note_pad execution privilege (unix), then:

  note_pad pull/push docs

- The device must be connected
- Be sure to kill the app before pushing
- !!! WARNING Target locations are emptied WARNING !!!

